
## FILE FIND FIRST, REPRODUCE SECOND

If your analysis names a concrete security defect at `file:function:line`
with a reviewer-actionable rationale (issue class + impact + caller control),
**write `{{ results_dir }}/findings/FIND-NNN-<slug>/report.md` immediately**
— before, or in parallel with, the reproducer loop below. Use the absolute
path; a relative `findings/...` resolves against your current cwd, which
may have drifted into the source tree after a `cd` and would silently
mis-route the finding. Filing a FIND is **not** contingent on a sanitizer crash,
a runnable testcase, or web-reachability (see
`.agents/references/session-rules.md` "FIND Quality Bar"). If a reproducer
later lands, link the testcase into the FIND directory or open a CRASH that
references the FIND id.

**Why this matters:** source-only strategies (S2 invariant-negation,
S3 spec-vs-impl, S5 lifetime/state, S8 property-based) routinely identify
concrete defects before — or without ever achieving — an ASan crash.
Deferring the FIND until reproduction succeeds loses the finding when the
agent rotates, the iteration ends, or the testcase hits a coverage/build wall.

**Required FIND content** (anything missing → not a FIND, keep as a state note):
1. `file:function:line` (or endpoint/config key for non-code defects)
2. Named issue class (memory-safety / auth / injection / info-disclosure / crypto / race / boundary-violation / logic / …)
3. Rationale — what is wrong, impact, caller control. A reviewer can act on it.

**Skip filing** when the issue is pure correctness, data-integrity,
robustness, or spec-deviation without a security implication — the harness
gate quarantines non-security FINDs.

**Exception — work card with a pre-filed FIND:** if your assigned work
card carries a `find_id` (rendered in the card as a "PRE-FILED FIND"
block), the FIND already exists in `{{ results_dir }}/findings/<find_id>/`.
Augment that dir — never create a new `FIND-NNN-<slug>/` for the same
defect. The pre-filed id is the canonical record; double-filing inflates
the benchmark count and breaks cluster dedup.

**Optional but encouraged — `patch.diff`.** When your fix is a surgical
diff (a missing check, a corrected size, an inverted predicate),
save it as a file named exactly `patch.diff` in the FIND directory
alongside `report.md`. `bin/enrich-report` is the sole writer of the
`## Patch` section and will inline the sibling diff on render — so
**do not write a `## Patch` section in `report.md` yourself**. Same
filename and rule apply for CRASH directories. Capture with the
target's VCS (`git -C "$TARGET_ROOT" diff -- path/to/file > "$DIR/patch.diff"`
or `hg -R "$TARGET_ROOT" diff path/to/file > "$DIR/patch.diff"`); save
whenever `git apply --check` / `hg import --no-commit` dry-run succeeds.
Build/repro confirmation is a quality upgrade, not a gate. When the
fix is non-surgical (ABI rename, signature change, API replacement),
omit `patch.diff` entirely and add a `## Fix Direction` prose section
instead — the exporter marks the bundle `Advisory: yes` so reviewers
know the omission is intentional.
